race.description: Southside Sessions Music Festival 17 Jan Handicap
race.comment: Wide open race with many coming off excuses. ATAEGINA (5) is one such galloper who will find this far easier than the city class race last start when beaten five lengths. Best form stacks up and in this far easier grade can quickly atone. MASTERFUL (3) hasn't been far away at last couple. Goes well here on home track and aided by the claim. Drawn for a soft run on the inside and gets chance to find some form. QUEEN BEIRA (7) has been thereabouts in two runs back but worth noting is a third-up winner. Drawn well and should be ready to fire. GABLE (9) is an interesting runner who is mixing distances, racing over 1400m two back then back to 1000m last time. Has some decent form in tougher company last time in at about a mile and was tested in stakes class. Jumps back up in trip but worth including. BANCORY BAY (2) wasn't far away last start and should be very competitive.
